FileDialog/FolderBrowserDialog should fall back to legacy dialog on COMException

### Problem Description

When "Folder" or "File" option selected in the "Source Selection", there is a COMException thrown in Window Server Core editions. 
When instantiating the COM object fails, the dialog should automatically fall back to the legacy file dialog, which seems to be done by most native applications like notepad.exe. The fix is relative easy as you can work around the issue by catching COMException and disabling AutoUpgradeEnabled:
        try
        {
            dialog.ShowDialog();
        }
        catch (COMException) when (dialog.AutoUpgradeEnabled)
        {
            dialog.AutoUpgradeEnabled = false;
            try
            {
                dialog.ShowDialog();
            }
            finally
            {
                dialog.AutoUpgradeEnabled = true;
            }
        }
