mark values are not correct after forcing columnbreak in multicol

## Brief outline of the bug

Update mark after using `\columnbreak`, the value of `\botmark` is not correct.

## Minimal example showing the bug

```latex
\RequirePackage{latexbug}       % <--should be always the first line (see CONTRIBUTING)!
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage{multicol}
\makeatletter
\def\@oddhead{\firstmark\hfil\botmark}
\let\@evenhead\@oddhead
\begin{document}

\begin{multicols}{2}
A. \mark{{.}{A}}

\columnbreak % remove this, head will be correct

B. \mark{{.}{B}}
\end{multicols}

\end{document}
```

## Log file (required) and possibly PDF file  
[demo.log](https://github.com/latex3/latex2e/files/12494706/demo8.log)

## My understanding

According to my understanding, `multicol` is using `\get@keptmarks` to extract marks, if the vbox contains a force-break and a mark after this, then the mark would lost.

